. Also discuss management: what to do if the stock shoots up (perhaps you’re okay selling, or you roll the call). This episode emphasizes that this strategy can generate significant extra income (cite Lyn Alden’s data that covered call premiums can be 2-3x the dividend yield
) but also notes the cap on upside. A brief case study could be mentioned of a stock that traded flat for a year – an investor doing covered calls would have profited from premiums whereas a holder just got a small dividend.
