Intro to liquidity & QE/QT at a narrative level.

Connect: “These macro drivers explain why you might shift sectors/factors.”

Level 4 – Leverage, futures, volatility
Option leverage, futures, vol trades, advanced risk management.

New:

Deeper sector/factor rotation using macro signals + options/futures.

Liquidity as a tradable concept (careful positioning around liquidity events, funding stress, etc.).

Linking rates, liquidity, and vol into a coherent regime framework.

Level 5 – Hedge-fund-ish but retail-accessible
Tail risk hedging, structured products, factor tilts, managed futures, vol arbitrage.

New:

Business-cycle/factor rotation done in a rules-based, institutional style.

Liquidity + rates + vol integrated into a full macro + quant playbook (e.g. your “all-weather plus opportunistic tilts” framework).

